Name: ord
Description: Return the Unicode code point for a one-character string

Name: id
Description: Return the identity of an object

Name: functools.reduce
Description: Apply a function of two arguments cumulatively to the items of a sequence

Name: inspect.getsourcelines
Description: Return a list of source lines and starting line number for an object.

Name: dict.setdefault
Description: D.get(k,d), also set D[k]=d if k not in D

Name: collections.namedtuple
Description: Returns a new subclass of tuple with named fields

Name: itertools.compress
Description: Return data elements corresponding to true selector elements. Forms a shorter iterator from selected data elements using the selectors to coose the daya elements
Example: compress(data, selectors) --> iterator over selected data

Name: itertools.permutations
Description: Return successive r-length permutations of elements in the iterable.

Name: filter
Description: Return an iterator yielding those items of iterable for which function(item) is true.  If function is None, return the items that are true.
Example: filter(function or None, iterable) --> filter object

Name: getattr
Description: Get a named attribute from an object
